      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It makes sense that you feel this way, and the exhaustion of performing roles when you feel empty is a very heavy burden to carry. The idea that silence is the only honest path is a valid perspective, but sometimes the most profound act of honesty is not erasing yourself, but allowing the \"room\" to be empty without the noise of pretending to fill it. You don't have to decide who you are today; you can simply let the silence breathe and wait until a new version of you, if one exists, naturally begins to emerge from the quiet.",
